Package: cryptRopen
Title: Industrialized Pseudonymization of Variables Across Datasets
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Daniel", "Rakotomalala", , "rakdanielh@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Deterministic pseudonymization of variables in heterogeneous
    datasets, driven by a single Excel mask describing which columns to
    hash in each input file. Values are normalized (upper-case, trim,
    internal whitespace removal) and hashed with a user-provided salt via
    the 'digest' package; the default algorithm is MD5, any algorithm
    supported by 'digest' is accepted. The transformation is one-way and
    deterministic, so derived datasets can be shared without exposing the
    originals while joins on the pseudonymized columns remain possible.
    The high-level crypt_r() workflow processes the mask rows in parallel
    via the 'mirai' framework and returns a non-blocking job handle with
    status, wait and collect companions; an 'arrow'-backed streaming
    engine handles parquet and CSV inputs whose size exceeds available
    RAM. Suitable for GDPR-style pseudonymization, not for
    confidentiality-bearing encryption.
